<Content>I honestly have to say, I'm really not impressed. For the last three days in a row, I have purchased and had to return three different mp3 players! This Philips being the last I bought. The first two were 4GB RCA's, (sorely, I bought these at Walmart for $139.00) and finally the third was this Philips version which I purchased from Circuit City (this time with their 2-year warranty!)  Each one of these had the exact same problem--A defected earphone connection!! I mean 'come on', this is ridiculous--I could half-way expect this from Walmart, but getting it from a more reliable source like Circuit City and paying $199.00--thats $60.00 more for a so-called better product, and 'still' getting the same problem is... well, lets just say that its an understatement to call it frustrating! My advice to everybody is this: If your gonna purchase this Philips or any mp3 or ipod then do yourself a favor- Go to a 'more reliable' source that offers inexpensive extra warranty coverage-- it is definitely worth it since Philips tech support is time-consuming and nearly useless (this trouble is not uncommon even among other brands)and your bound to have problems with pretty much 'any' digital audio device sooner or later. "GOOD LUCK"!   
<Overall>3

