<Product Name>Philips HDD1630 6 GB MP3 Player
<Title>Excellent Player If you update it.
<Date>Wed Aug 16 00:00:00 CST 2006
<Content>I started off with an Ipod mini 4 GB. I was very happy with it until it busted on me. Internal chip became unsoldered. Very difficult to repair. I searched around for MP3 players with approximately the same space. I will never get a nano because of the cost. The Philips MP3 player has a great storage capacity for the money.  When I first got this player, I was dissapointed. It had tremendous lag. Skipping to the next track would take about 5 seconds. It seemed very sluggish. I did some searching and decided to update the firmware to V 2.1. Since the update, the player seems to be working great. It made a huge difference in the response time of the player.   As for the battery life.... I do not get the 17 hours that they advertise. But I didn't get the 18 hours that the ipod mini claims either. I like using the features of eq enhancements, shuffle, etc. I would say I get approx 8 hours of use. It is a very acceptable amount of time considering the battery draining factors I throw into the mix.  Overall I would recommend this player. Best storage capacity for the price. It seems to be more durable than ipods.  
<Overall>4

