<Review ID>3027752
<Product Name>Philips HDD1630 6 GB MP3 Player
<Title>Not As Cool As It Looks . . .
<Date>Wed Nov 23 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>Unfortunately, this item is nowhere near as good as it should be - There are a few good things about it, but the negatives definitely overshadow the positives - especially for me because my previous MP3 player was a CREATIVE NANO which was simple click and drag using Windows without installing special software to add files to the device - This is NOT the case with the Philips GoGear - I'll try to break it down to prove why I gave this item such a low rating.  Positives -   1.) Cool design 2.) Capable of displaying your digital images on a color screen  Negatives - 1.) Loading music is anything but simple because installation of the factory software is mandatory in order to add files to the device. 2.) When connected to a PC's USB port, the device isn't assigned a temporary drive letter for easy file transfer using drag and drop. 3.) The quality of the color screen is comparable to an early color cell phone - (something similar to the Nokia 0001 model)  Overall, if you're just about the music I would recommend the Creative ZEN NANO - If you want performance with looks I would recommend an Apple Ipod NANO it has the ability to display your digital images in color and can hold massive amounts of music.  
<Overall>2

