<Title>Looks can be deceiving!
<Date>Thu Jun 22 00:00:00 CST 2006
<Content>As another reviewer stated, the Phillips HDD16530 is a piece of (....)! I thought I was lucky when I got this item for $99 as an opened product, but I was soooo wrong. I had problems with all my songs disappearing from my device. I had to reload everything 2x. When it got to the 3rd attempt of reloading, it froze! Phillips' technical support was not helpful at all! They suggested I take it back where I received it. When I took it back I wound up paying an additional $100 to get another like it (why I did that, I don't know). Well, this one did fine for almost 2 weeks until I began to add more songs.... the same problems persisted, lost all my songs (by this time I'm up to 1,000), and it froze! I loved the look, the sound, and its size, but the navigation buttons were too sensitive which frustrated me to no end! I thought the headphones were uncomfortable. Needless to say when it froze again, I didn't bother with technical support. I just packed it up and took it back as well. I now have a Zen Microphoto 8 GB by Creative (So far so good). It took no time to transfer my downloads and cd's, plus it was the same price as the Phillips! I did notice that the retail store I purchased the Phillips didn't have any on display, even when I got the "in box". They had it stored underneath their counter. It all makes me wonder about the number of complaints and defects they've received, not to mention Phillips themselves. In a nutshell, looks CAN be deceiving. It's plagued with too many problems.  
